reflected very badly on their
Olympics.

20:19.118 --> 20:23.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They feel very aggrieved,
because all the
focused was on Ryan Lochte
having said that

20:23.722 --> 20:24.890 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he had been assaulted.

20:24.924 --> 20:27.326 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it made these Olympics look
very bad.

20:27.359 --> 20:32.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now they feel that he lied,
he misrepresented
what happened and that an
apology, quite simply,

20:32.598 --> 20:34.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is not quite enough.

20:34.166 --> 20:37.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the apology that he gave is
being received
here as not really an apology.

20:37.903 --> 20:41.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They don't feel that he admitted
what they
feel is the truth, which is that
he lied.

20:41.741 --> 20:47.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Lulu, is there
still any potential
legal or diplomatic implications
to come?

20:47.546 --> 20:53.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: Well, I
think the diplomatic
implications are that -- have
sort of been

20:53.385 --> 20:54.753 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
resolved.

20:54.787 --> 20:57.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Certainly, three of the swimmers
are on their
way back to the States.

20:57.156 --> 21:00.326 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we understand that the other
will be leaving
shortly.

21:00.359 --> 21:05.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, therefore, I think it
has been smoothed
over.

21:05.231 --> 21:06.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The police do feel that they did
their job.

21:06.665 --> 21:08.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They investigated this.

21:08.501 --> 21:12.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They showed to the world that,
in fact, what
Ryan Lochte and his cohorts said
had happened

21:12.271 --> 21:14.140 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
had not happened.

21:14.173 --> 21:18.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I think the Brazilian
government, Rio's
government and the police feel
that they have

21:18.777 --> 21:22.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
shown that they are responsible
and that this
is a place that has the rule of
law.

21:22.414 --> 21:25.017 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I don't think it will go any
further diplomatically.

21:25.050 --> 21:28.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, so,
Christine, back
to sports now.

21:28.087 --> 21:34.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, you and I talked
about swimmers
in a different context, swimmers
in the pool,

21:34.059 --> 21:35.828 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and about gymnastics.

21:35.861 --> 21:41.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this time, I think we want
to talk about
one guy, this great runner,
Usain Bolt.

21:41.400 --> 21:43.335 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Oh,
absolutely, Jeff.

21:43.369 --> 21:47.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for all the terrible things
that the Americans
did -- and they will get
suspended for it

21:48.007 --> 21:54.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
almost for sure -- then you have
got the joy
of Usain Bolt, and winning the
100-meter for

21:54.146 --> 21:55.447 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the third time.

21:55.481 --> 21:59.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No man has ever done that
before, Beijing,
London and now Rio.

21:59.685 --> 22:01.053 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He had to come from behind.

22:01.086 --> 22:04.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Justin Gatlin had the lead with
about 75 meters
to go.

22:04.490 --> 22:05.925 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
No problem.

22:05.958 --> 22:08.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Usain Bolt could not dance
and prance
and look around at the end.

22:08.327 --> 22:11.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He had to pretty much run
through the tape,
the finish line.

22:11.797 --> 22:17.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then coming back in the 200
meters, this
is a difficult double under any
circumstances.

22:17.236 --> 22:23.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Usain Bolt turned 30 on Sunday,
the day these
Games end.

22:23.309 --> 22:25.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he's not a young man in this
sport.

22:25.044 --> 22:28.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as we know, he had a
hamstring injury,
and there's been a lot of
questions.

22:28.113 --> 22:34.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, he's now done the 100, the
200, huge win,
and if he gets the relay, the
Jamaican relay,

22:34.653 --> 22:42.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he will have an incredible
triple-triple,
three events, three different
Olympic Games,

22:42.595 --> 22:44.296 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and winning in them all.

22:44.330 --> 22:47.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has cemented himself as one
of the greatest
Olympians of all time.

22:47.466 --> 22:51.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, briefly,
Christine, because
we have also seen the continued
dominance

22:51.503 --> 22:54.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of American women, including in
the medal
count.

22:54.206 --> 22:55.274 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: Absolutely.

22:55.307 --> 22:57.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Team Title IX, we saw it start
in London,
Jeff.

22:57.576 --> 22:59.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We talked about it then.

22:59.411 --> 23:02.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're talking about it again
now, Title IX,
signed by Richard Nixon in June
of '72, working

23:02.948 --> 23:07.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it way through the generations,
creating of
all these great athletes, the
girl next door

23:07.586 --> 23:09.688 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who grows up and wins the
Olympic U.S. medals.

23:09.722 --> 23:14.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. women are dominating,
winning about 60,
61, 62 percent of the U.S. gold
medals and

23:14.960 --> 23:18.163 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also well over 50 percent of the
U.S. total
medals.

23:18.197 --> 23:19.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And get used to it.

23:19.331 --> 23:21.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's going to keep happening
over and over
again.

23:21.467 --> 23:25.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, so, Lulu, I
want to come
back to you, because we -- you
and I talked

23:25.404 --> 23:30.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
several days before the Games
started about
all the apprehension, lack of
preparation,

23:30.276 --> 23:32.111 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Brazil's economic problems.

23:32.144 --> 23:36.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You even said to me, I remember,
at that point
that locals were ready to have
it done with,

23:36.548 --> 23:38.183 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
even before it had started.

23:38.217 --> 23:41.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what's your sense now of how
people have
responded?

23:41.720 --> 23:43.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How has it gone over there?

23:43.289 --> 23:46.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: I think you
can look
at this in two ways.

23:46.225 --> 23:50.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Certainly, when you speak to
average Brazilians,
they have fallen in love with
the Olympics.

23:50.729 --> 23:55.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have really greeted it with
a great deal
of joy, once the opening
ceremony happened.

23:55.467 --> 24:00.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They really enjoyed seeing all
the people
here, and they enjoyed having
the athletes

24:00.506 --> 24:02.374 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
compete.

24:02.408 --> 24:05.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, on the other hand, of
course, there have
been a number of problems,
leaving Ryan Lochte

24:05.878 --> 24:09.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
aside, the fact that he might
have invented
what happened to him, but there
have been

24:09.348 --> 24:14.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
assaults, there have been
organizational snafus,
empty seats, slow ticket sales.

24:14.586 --> 24:19.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I think the epitaph for these
Olympics
is going to be mixed.

24:19.692 --> 24:23.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think people will look at this
on the one
hand and say the Brazilians did
the best that

24:23.062 --> 24:27.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they could under very difficult
circumstances,
but, on the other hand, this
wasn't an Olympics

24:27.700 --> 24:30.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that a lot of people think was
up to standard.

24:30.069 --> 24:34.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, briefly,
still to come,
there are some problems, Lulu,
with the Paralympics.

24:34.373 --> 24:40.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: Well, this
actually is
a growing controversy, a great
scandal.

24:40.045 --> 24:45.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Basically, the Paralympic Games,
which did
so well in the last Summer
Olympic Games in

24:45.884 --> 24:50.789 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
London, are now facing
unprecedented -- an
unprecedented budget crisis.

24:50.823 --> 24:54.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Basically, we have been told
today that maybe
10 teams at least won't be able
to make it

24:54.993 --> 25:00.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here because Rio 2016 Organizing
Committee
doesn't have the money to pay
for them to

25:00.232 --> 25:01.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
come.

25:01.233 --> 25:02.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're going to be slashing
venues.

25:02.301 --> 25:04.670 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're going to be slashing
transportation.

25:04.703 --> 25:10.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so what the head, the
president of the
Paralympics Committee said today
was that,

25:10.309 --> 25:15.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in his 50-plus years of being
involved in
this movement, he had never
faced a situation

25:15.681 --> 25:16.648 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like this.

25:16.682 --> 25:20.252 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is an absolute scandal, he
said.

25:20.285 --> 25:23.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he's very concerned about
how these Paralympic
Games will go off.

25:23.689 --> 25:27.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Lulu
Garcia-Navarro,
Christine Brennan, thank you
both very much

25:27.626 --> 25:28.961 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from Rio.

25:28.994 --> 25:34.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINE BRENNAN: Thank you,
Jeff.

25:34.333 --> 25:38.570 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: You're
welcome.

25:38.604 --> 25:41.573 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

25:41.607 --> 25:47.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": a
master filmmaker
on his work and new documentary;
and Mark

25:47.413 --> 25:49.448 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Shields and Jennifer Rubin.

25:49.481 --> 25:56.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: The world's newest
country, South
Sudan, established in 2011,
again stands on

25:56.755 --> 25:58.357 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the brink of civil war.

25:58.390 --> 26:03.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A peace deal signed last year
between rival
governing factions is in
tatters.

26:03.495 --> 26:09.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More than one-sixth of the
country's 12 million
citizens have been displaced,
and the humanitarian

26:09.601 --> 26:12.604 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
crisis there is worsening by the
day.

26:12.638 --> 26:14.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
John Yang has the story.

26:14.573 --> 26:19.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: For that view, we
turn to photographer
Sebastian Rich, who has covered
conflict zones

26:19.211 --> 26:20.512 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for more than four decades.

26:20.546 --> 26:23.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has been to South Sudan many
times.

26:23.482 --> 26:28.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is there now on assignment
for UNICEF,
the United Nations children's
agency.

26:28.720 --> 26:31.590 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He joins us now via Skype from
Juba, the capital.

26:31.623 --> 26:34.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sebastian, thanks for joining
thus evening.

26:34.927 --> 26:40.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First of all, tell us how it
feels now, what
the situation is like on the
ground now.

26:40.265 --> 26:44.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEBASTIAN RICH, Photojournalist:
Well, the
situation is a little more tense
than it was,

26:44.069 --> 26:45.571 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
obviously, before the recent
fighting.

26:45.604 --> 26:50.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The recent fighting has put the
people, the
ordinary people in the street.

26:50.909 --> 26:52.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're much more tense than
they were.

26:52.444 --> 26:54.246 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's not so many friendly
faces.

26:54.279 --> 26:59.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you walk in the streets of
Juba now, you're
not greeted the same way you
were a couple

26:59.384 --> 27:03.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of months ago or even a year
ago, when I came
last year.

27:03.088 --> 27:10.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And how is this
affecting the children
that you're covering, that
you're there watching,

27:10.863 --> 27:15.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
looking at behalf on UNICEF,
particularly
the issues of malnutrition?

27:15.300 --> 27:20.272 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEBASTIAN RICH: Well, it's
affecting the children
very badly.

27:20.305 --> 27:27.880 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And there's 250,000, a
quarter-of-a-million
children suffering from severe
acute malnutrition.

27:27.913 --> 27:32.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's not including the
children who
just got malnutrition, the first
stages of.

27:32.885 --> 27:38.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what's happened is that the
children who
were actually starting to
recover from severe

27:38.156 --> 27:42.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
acute malnutrition before this
recent fighting,
when the fighting happened,
those children

27:42.694 --> 27:46.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
couldn't come back to the
hospitals to get
their follow-up treatment and
children that

27:46.732 --> 27:50.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had started to get malnutrition
couldn't get
to the hospitals either.

27:50.569 --> 27:56.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So now we have this huge
increase in malnutrition
and severe cases of
malnutrition.

27:56.041 --> 28:00.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And UNICEF is trying its very,
very best to
keep on top of this disaster.

28:00.512 --> 28:05.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And you spent time
some today,
you were telling me, with a
young girl who

28:05.751 --> 28:07.386 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
actually has been making
progress.

28:07.419 --> 28:10.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And is there danger that this
could reverse
what's happening?

28:10.989 --> 28:12.558 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SEBASTIAN RICH: Yes.

28:12.591 --> 28:14.459 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not all bad news.

28:14.493 --> 28:17.863 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are wonderful individual
cases.

28:17.896 --> 28:22.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last year, I photographed a
little in a hospital
in Juba.

28:22.734 --> 28:24.102 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And she was on death's door.

28:24.136 --> 28:25.971 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She was a tiny little stick
insect.

28:26.004 --> 28:27.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I stayed with her for a
couple of weeks.

28:27.539 --> 28:30.142 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And she got a bit better and bit
better.

28:30.175 --> 28:34.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, today, six months later,
when I came
back, I photographed her and
filmed her with

28:34.746 --> 28:38.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her family, singing and dancing
to tunes on
my iPhone.

28:38.884 --> 28:44.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it was fantastic to see a
success story
for once in this mess here.

28:44.623 --> 28:49.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And is there danger
that, with
this increased tension, that
some of that

28:49.294 --> 28:51.530 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
progress could be reversed or
lost?

28:51.563 --> 28:55.901 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SEBASTIAN RICH: Yes, of course.

28:55.934 --> 28:56.969 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Children will die.

28:57.002 --> 28:59.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, I don't see how you can
sugarcoat
it.

28:59.204 --> 29:04.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you don't get treated for
severe acute
malnutrition, you will die.

29:04.409 --> 29:05.677 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's not only malnutrition.

29:05.711 --> 29:07.879 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's complications with
malnutrition.

29:07.913 --> 29:12.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of these children have on
top of that
tuberculosis and malaria.

29:12.384 --> 29:15.420 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, yes, put it very simply,
they will die.

29:15.454 --> 29:21.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And another area that
this sort
of increased tension threatens
are child soldiers.

29:21.960 --> 29:29.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have seen reports that,
perhaps in preparation
for tensions, that the
recruitment of child

29:29.301 --> 29:31.637 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
soldiers is on the increase
again.

29:31.670 --> 29:35.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have actually been watching
programs where
they have been trying to take
them out of

29:35.907 --> 29:37.409 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
those -- of that situation.

29:37.442 --> 29:39.244 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SEBASTIAN RICH: Yes.

29:39.277 --> 29:44.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, once again, the renewed
fighting has
caused more problems, because
now much more

29:44.449 --> 29:50.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
children will be coerced into
trying to be
forced into joining armed
groups.

29:50.689 --> 29:55.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But UNICEF, once again, has been
very, very
successful in taking these
children who have

